text:
Once again, this administration is undermining scientific credibility and eroding public trust. Suggesting a link between Tylenol and autism, without credible evidence, spreads fear instead of facts. Reckless statements from the President and RFK Jr. that ignore established science only create confusion for families.

As an occupational therapist, I’ve seen how deeply misinformation can harm patients and parents. We must trust the guidance of medical experts and ensure public health decisions are rooted in facts, not politics and pseudoscience. Families deserve clarity, compassion, and the truth.

The President of the United States must lead with unity, not division. The Office of the President should represent all Americans, and a leader who says "I hate my opponents" undermines the values that unite us as a nation.

In times of division, our leaders must strive to bring us together because what unites us will always be stronger than what divides us. 

We are better than this.

https://t.co/rHDJ0xTgFR

Today in Amherst, I stood with patients, workers, and community leaders outside Buffalo Therapy Services – one of several Kaleida facilities set to close because of Trump and Congressional Republicans’ Medicaid cuts. 

These closures are exactly what we warned would happen when the GOP forced through Trump’s Big Ugly Law. Facilities shutting down, costs rising, and care disappearing. 

As an occupational therapist, I know the life-changing work done here. The patients who rely on this care deserve better than partisan games in Washington. Congressional Republicans need to cancel the cuts, extend the ACA enhanced tax credits, and fix the healthcare crisis they’ve created. 

Lives are on the line.

As Jewish families in Western New York and across the country gather to welcome Rosh Hashanah, I extend my warmest wishes for a joyous, healthy, and peaceful new year. 

May this season of reflection and renewal bring hope, unity, and blessings to all. Shanah Tovah!

I’m so blessed to be able to call Mary Kennedy my mother! 

She has spent her entire life spreading kindness and compassion, and helping people in need! She is a shining example of goodness and love in the world! 

Happy Birthday, Mom!!! We love you!!! https://t.co/RI1lydc36k

On #NationalTradesmanDay, we honor the men and women whose skill and grit built Western New York and our nation.

Thank you for your craftsmanship, your union strength, and your commitment to moving our region forward.

As a proud member of @Labor_Caucus, I’ll always fight for your rights and livelihoods.

Attention all high school students: Interested in applying to a service academy? 

Join my office and the Office of @SenGillibrand on October 2 at 6:00 PM for our annual Service Academy Night. Learn about the application process and hear directly from Service Academy representatives.

I had the privilege of joining @RepJeffries and @SpeakerPelosi to honor Bob Fischer, a fellow South Buffalo native whose steady presence for House Democrats has been appreciated by all for nearly forty years.

Through the passage of landmark legislation, presidential addresses, and moments of national triumph and tragedy, Bob has been behind the scenes doing the critical legwork that often goes unnoticed.

Congratulations on your retirement Bob – I wish you nothing but the best!
Democrats are united to #CanceltheCuts. https://t.co/QBAAWMLXdk

Trump’s FCC pressure campaign to cancel Jimmy Kimmel’s late night show is a deeply troubling and un-American abuse of power. In this country, free speech is a fundamental, constitutionally protected right.

We continue to see a dangerous pattern from this administration: using public office not to serve the people, but to punish critics. Government intimidation of broadcast networks and censorship of alternative viewpoints puts us on a dark path that we must all come together, regardless of party, to resist as Americans.

Our democracy is founded on the principle of being able to openly debate ideas, even controversial or unpopular ones, without fear of political violence or government retribution. I’ll always stand up for the First Amendment and against any attempt to weaponize the government against free expression.

Grateful to join so many proud Western New Yorkers in Washington last night for Buffalo Nite!

Buffalo’s story is one of grit, resilience, and community – and our future is brighter than ever. From our world-class universities and skilled workforce to bold investments in infrastructure and transit, Buffalo is proving to the nation what real leadership looks like. 

There is no place home, and no people like Buffalonians. Proud to represent our hometown in the nation’s capitol.

The House unanimously passed the Honoring our Heroes Act, commonsense legislation I introduced to ensure that more veterans are eligible to receive a VA-issued headstone.

This is a meaningful victory for veterans and their families. It guarantees that their service and sacrifice will be honored with the dignity and remembrance they deserve, now and for generations to come.

When disaster strikes, preparedness is not optional – it’s essential. Today, I recognized National Preparedness Month on the House floor to emphasize the critical work done by FEMA.

As Ranking Member of the Emergency Management & Technology Subcommittee, I am committed to ensuring FEMA stands ready to help our communities respond, recover, and rebuild.

South Buffalo has always been a place defined by hard work, strong families, and a deep sense of pride. The McKinley Parkway Historic District has been named New York’s largest historic district, covering more than 5,000 homes, churches, and community landmarks.

This recognition celebrates the generations of Irish immigrants and working families who built South Buffalo into an amazing place to raise a family and call home. It also brings new opportunities for residents to invest in their homes with historic tax credits that will keep our community strong for years to come. I am thrilled to see our community's legacy honored in such a meaningful way.

Congratulations to Dr. Tripathi on his remarkable tenure at @UBuffalo.

Throughout my time in public service, he has been a steadfast partner in advancing the University at Buffalo, reaching new heights in education, research, and, most recently, as a leader in AI innovation, as well as leading the charge for successful passage of SUNY 2020.

As he prepares to step down in July 2026, his lasting impact on the University and our community is clear. All of WNY is deeply grateful for his service.

Today is National Voter Registration Day, so if you are not yet registered to vote, you can register online at the New York Board of Elections! The best way to make sure your voice is heard in politics at all levels is to vote. Elections take place every year, including at the local level, so make sure you’re able to participate by registering to vote!

https://t.co/hiVkyMJGAV

Happy Hispanic Heritage Month! This month, we celebrate and honor the cultural heritage of our Hispanic-American communities.

Our region is made stronger and our culture is made richer by the values and traditions of Western New York’s Hispanic communities.

This month and every month, let us honor their contributions, uplift their voices, and continue building a community where every culture is celebrated.

Proud to join the Doyle Fire District today to celebrate the completion of a $240,000 grant I secured as a State Senator to upgrade radios for Doyle Hose #1 and #2 and purchase two state-of-the-art fire suppression systems for electric vehicle battery fires.

Our volunteer firefighters put their lives on the line for us, we owe them the tools and technology to do their jobs safely and effectively. 

This investment strengthens Cheektowaga’s emergency response and ensures our first responders have the resources they need to protect our community.

It has been 21 years since the bipartisan Federal Assault Weapons Ban expired – and America has paid the price in countless innocent lives lost to gun violence.

Since then, we’ve seen mass shootings become more frequent and more deadly, devastating families and communities across this country. We know this policy worked – gun deaths dropped while the ban was in place. 

It is long overdue that Congress reinstates this common sense law to keep weapons of war off our streets.

Yesterday in New York, I was reminded of the perilous moments in our nation’s history – and how, in the face of tragedy, Americans have put aside our differences to unite around our shared values and love of country. 

This year, we’ve seen the lives of public servants and political figures on both sides of the aisle cut short by extremism. Political violence has no place in America. We resolve our differences at the ballot box, not with bullets. 

May we honor the memory of those we lost on 9/11 by following our better angels and choosing to see one another’s shared humanity.

I’m here at Ground Zero as we commemorate the 24th anniversary of the September 11th terrorist attacks.

The memories of those we lost that terrible day continue to live on. Let us embrace the best ideals of America as we continue to heal.

God bless America. https://t.co/RULSq57IgK

Our nation was forever changed 24 years ago today. On this solemn day we remember the nearly 3,000 lives lost on September 11, 2001, and honor the courage of the first responders who ran toward danger without hesitation. 

We stand with the families who still carry the weight of that day, and with the countless men and women who have served our nation in the years since.

New York will never forget. America will never forget. May we continue to honor their memory through unity, service, and love.

God bless the United States of America.
Political violence has no place in America. I'm horrified by the reported shooting of Charlie Kirk today in Utah. Congress must act to end the scourge of gun violence in our country.

Herb Bellamy, Jr. is a trailblazer whose 33 years of service at the Buffalo Sewer Authority and lifelong commitment to equity, opportunity, and community, have left an indelible mark on Western New York.

Thank you, Herb, for your friendship and for leading with heart and integrity. Wishing you nothing but the best in your next chapter.

FEMA must be strengthened, not weakened. Every region faces its own disasters – from blizzards in Buffalo to hurricanes in Florida – and no American should worry whether their government will be there to help them recover.

As Ranking Member of the Emergency Management & Technology Subcommittee, I’m committed to ensuring FEMA has the tools and resources it needs to deliver a strong, coordinated response.

Grateful to have partners like @USRepKCastor and @RepDWStweets in this effort.

Honored to stand with @RepBrownley and our colleagues to highlight the urgent need to prevent firearm suicides in our nation.

Designating September 9th as National Firearm Suicide Prevention Day is about raising awareness, promoting safe storage, and saving our loved ones. 

As a member of the House Veterans Affairs Committee, I’m committed to combating the alarming rate of veteran suicides, including those involving firearms. It is our sacred responsibility to ensure that our heroes, families, friends, and neighbors have all available resources and support in a time of crisis.
Back right where he belongs. Go Bills! ❤️🦬💙 #MVP https://t.co/oKz1Rq6OqP

September 8, 1954 Ruby Bridges was born and just 6 years later she would become an icon for the Civil Rights movement.  

She became the first Black child to integrate an all-white elementary school in the South, walking bravely past angry crowds and into history.

May her birthday serve as a reminder of the power of courage and the ongoing fight for justice across our nation.

Happy International Literacy Day! Today we celebrate the power of books, learning, and community.

Literacy is not just about books, it is about the opportunity for every person to read, learn, and thrive. When we provide people with access to libraries, resources, and education, we open doors to create a more just and sustainable society.

Happy World Physical Therapy Day!

As an occupational therapist, I have a deep appreciation for the incredible work physical therapists do every day, and as the husband of an amazing PT, I've seen firsthand how their skill and dedication transform lives.

Today, we celebrate these vital healthcare professionals who help people regain mobility, manage pain, and live more independent lives. They are essential partners in patient care, and I'm proud to champion their work. Thank you, PTs, for all that you do!
Take it from a Kennedy who has actually practiced healthcare: RFK is hellbent on turning back the clock on vaccine policies and it will cost lives. He must resign.

For the first time since the pandemic, and once again on Donald Trump’s watch, we lost jobs in June.

Firing the head of the Bureau of Labor Statistics didn’t change the facts on the ground: the policies of President Trump and Congressional Republicans are tanking the economy, stunting job growth, and hurting working-class families.

I was proud to stand alongside my colleagues, veterans, and advocates to oppose the Trump administration’s proposed rule that would strip veterans of essential reproductive health care and reinstate a near-total abortion ban at the VA.

We have an obligation to protect and expand healthcare for all Americans – especially those who have dedicated their lives to protecting our freedoms.

Big news from my alma mater, @DYouville!

This is a game-changer for Western New York and is a testament to the university’s vision and leadership.

This is a huge win for Buffalo and the future of healthcare in our community.

Congratulations to my friend Tim Herzog and everyone at @FlyingBison on 25 years!

Tim’s vision brought craft brewing back to Buffalo and helped spark a movement that’s now a cornerstone of Western New York’s culture and economy. Beyond brewing, his lifelong commitment to our community, small businesses, and mentoring the next generation continues to inspire.

Here’s to 25 years of Flying Bison — and many more to come. Sláinte!

Gene Vukelic was a dear friend, a Marine, a businessman, a devoted husband, father, grandfather, and great-grandfather. 

He was a man of deep faith and enormous generosity whose impact on Western New York will be felt for generations.
 
His life reminds us that true success lies in service to others. May Gene rest in peace.

The work of the nurses and healthcare professionals of @CWA1133  and @CWA1168  at Mercy Hospital is essential to ensuring safe, quality care for our community, and deserves fair pay, safe staffing, and strong benefits. 

As the son and grandson of nurses, the husband of a physical therapist, and an occupational therapist myself, I know firsthand the sacrifices caregivers make every single day. They are the backbone of our healthcare system – they deserve fair pay, safe staffing, and the benefits that allow them to care for their own families.

On this Labor Day, we honor the workers who continue to build this country – and the labor movement that has secured safer jobs, fairer pay, and dignity in the workplace. 

Unions are the backbone of America’s middle class and the guardians of our economy. When workers have a voice, families have stability, communities have resilience, and our nation is stronger. 

I will never stop standing shoulder to shoulder with organized labor, because an attack on unions is an attack on working people everywhere.

A 6-year-old in Buffalo just started first grade cancer-free thanks to CAR T-cell therapy at @RoswellPark. That isn’t just groundbreaking science – it is a miracle made possible by public investment in lifesaving research. 

This is exactly the kind of care @HouseDemocrats are fighting to protect. But right now, thanks to the largest healthcare cut in American history pushed by Trump and Congressional Republicans, breakthroughs like this are in jeopardy. 

I am fighting to make sure every child, every patient, and every family can get the care they deserve. Healthcare is not a luxury, it is a right.

Trump’s war on public service continues unabated, even as Labor Day approaches. The workers at NASA, the National Weather Service, and other impacted agencies keep us safe, advance cutting edge research, and ensure that the United States remains a global leader in technology and science. Americans deserve better.

https://t.co/EsyFxj97Yk

Twenty years ago, #HurricaneKatrina devastated New Orleans and the Gulf Coast – leaving behind loss, displacement, and difficult lessons about our nation’s preparedness.

Yet today, FEMA faces not only natural disasters, but a manufactured crisis of mismanagement that has weakened its mission from within – even as extreme weather grows more frequent and severe.

As Ranking Member of the Emergency Management & Technology Subcommittee, I’m committed to strengthening FEMA, restoring trust in our disaster response systems, and ensuring no community is ever left behind when disaster strikes.

Seventy years ago today, Emmet Till’s life was stolen by an act of racial hatred so brutal that it shocked the conscience of our nation.

His murder laid bare the ugly reality of racial violence in America and galvanized the Civil Rights Movement.

As we honor his memory today, we have a moral obligation to confront hate in all of its forms in order to build a future defined by equality and compassion.

Today marks 62 years since the March on Washington for Jobs and Freedom, a day when Dr. King’s dream rang out across the nation and changed the course of American history.

The fight for equality, dignity, and opportunity did not end in 1963 – it continues in our neighborhoods, our schools, and our workplaces.

Let us honor this anniversary by recommitting ourselves to the unfinished work of justice and freedom for all.

The good news: tourism in Western New York in 2024 set a record, creating jobs and driving our economy forward.

The bad news: Donald Trump’s policies threaten that progress.

We need to welcome our Canadian neighbors back with open arms, not with threats.

I am heartbroken by the news out of Minneapolis. As a parent, I cannot begin to imagine the pain that the victims and their families are enduring right now.

This is a tragedy that should shake every single one of us to our core. We cannot accept an America where children are gunned down in their schools, their neighborhoods, or anywhere else.

My prayers are with the families and the entire Minneapolis community. We must summon the courage to confront America’s gun violence epidemic and finally pass reform that will save innocent lives.

WNY’s families are already paying the price for Trump and Congressional Republicans’ Big Ugly Law. This law guts Medicaid, Medicare, and the ACA, all to hand tax breaks to billionaires.

As the only occupational therapist in Congress, I know just how devastating the closure of clinics will be for patients who rely on these services to recover, rebuild, and live with dignity.

Stripping away access to healthcare doesn’t make our nation stronger, it leaves our most vulnerable neighbors behind. Congressional Republicans are treating people’s lives as collateral damage.

I am heartbroken by the devastating crash on the New York State Thruway this afternoon. My prayers are with the victims, their families, and everyone affected by this tragedy. I am grateful for brave first responders caring for our community during this difficult time.

In my previous role as Chair of the State Senate Transportation Committee, I fought to create the State Touring Routes program, helping to more than triple the City of Buffalo’s road funding. Thrilled to see these dollars in action helping to strengthen our communities.

@MayorScanlon

In just one quarter, car manufacturers shelled out $11.7 BILLION due to Trump’s tariff costs –  a tax on American businesses, labor, and families.

That’s money that should be fueling paychecks, keeping prices down for consumers, and driving investment in American manufacturing – not being siphoned away by a reckless economic agenda.

Trump’s policies are putting our auto industry in neutral, not driving it forward. I’ll keep fighting for trade policies that lift up workers, strengthen supply chains, and protect America’s competitive edge.

Welcome home to the nearly 80 brave men and women of the 914th Air Refueling Wing at the Niagara Falls Air Reserve Station! After months of deployment in the Middle East, these reservists return to WNY with our deepest gratitude.

Their service and sacrifice, along with the strength of their families who carried on in their absence, remind us of the immense commitment required by those who keep our nation safe.

Today we cut the ribbon on @UBuffalo's  new Mobile Health Units – a project that will bring doctors, screenings, and care directly into neighborhoods across Buffalo.

For too long, inaccessibility has kept too many Western New Yorkers from getting the healthcare they deserve. These mobile units will help break down that barrier, meeting people where they are and delivering lifesaving, affordable care.

As an occupational therapist, I know firsthand the difference that timely, accessible care can make. Together, we’re building a healthier, more equitable future for Buffalo.

Thank you to @nationalgridus for committing $2 million to establish a new Clean Energy Experience Center and Clean Technology Lab right here at the @NorthlandWTC.

This state-of-the-art facility will give students hands-on training in renewable energy and clean tech, skills that will open doors to good-paying jobs, strengthen our unions, and ensure Western New York leads in the industries of tomorrow.

Northland has always been more than a training center – it’s a catalyst for opportunity and transformation. With this new commitment, we’re proving once again that Buffalo is ready to power the future.

Tom Golisano’s $50 million gift to Children’s Hospital is truly monumental for Buffalo and all of Western New York.

This investment will ensure world-class medical services for children and families in our community for generations to come.

On behalf of every Western New Yorker, I look forward to the continuation of excellent and life-changing care at the Golisano Children’s Hospital of Buffalo.

We had a great Saturday to celebrate the culture, heritage, and community at the 23rd Annual Puerto Rican and Hispanic Day Parade of WNY!

Western New York’s Puerto Rican and Hispanic communities enrich our neighborhoods with vibrant traditions, strong values, and immense contributions to every aspect of our cultural and economic life. 

I’m proud to always stand with you, celebrate with you, and fight for you in Washington.

This morning, I stood with childcare advocates to call out what parents already know: diapers, cribs, strollers, and formula are more expensive than ever. Trump’s reckless tariffs have only worsened this reality.

These costs are squeezing working families while Congressional Republicans gut healthcare, nutritional assistance, and threaten Social Security in order to hand out tax breaks to billionaires.

That’s why, alongside my colleagues in the @DadsCaucus, I’m fighting to put babies over billionaires and pass legislation that eliminates tariffs on baby products. Parenthood shouldn’t come with an extra Trump tax.

For 90 years, Social Security has been a lifeline for America’s seniors, veterans, families, and individuals with disabilities — a promise that after a lifetime of hard work, Americans can retire with dignity and know that they will not have to live in fear of poverty.  

The Trump administration’s push to dismantle and privatize Social Security would devastate millions who depend on it. We must protect Social Security for today’s retirees and for future generations.

Another huge step forward for the Buffalo Central Terminal’s reactivation. I was proud to get the ball rolling in 2018 by securing $5 million in state funding - the first major public funding for this site since its closure in the 1970s.

This progress brings us closer to a vision of a Terminal that anchors the Broadway-Fillmore community and benefits all of Western New York. Kudos to the Central Terminal Restoration Corporation and the hardworking construction teams who made this possible.

https://t.co/JbTTKwXEln

@CentralTerminal @RCWJRF @EmpireStateDev

As the son and grandson of a nurse, I know how hard the team at the Buffalo VA works each and every day to provide world-class care for those who have fought and bled for our freedoms. 

This is just the latest move by the Trump Administration in their ongoing campaign to punish federal workers. I stand united with our unionized VA workforce in this fight, now and into the future. 

President Trump and Secretary Collins should be ashamed.

https://t.co/ioIJMfzRGS

As the Trump administration and Congressional Republicans work to gut funding to VA’s across the nation, House Democrats are fighting back to say hell no to these cuts. 

Our veterans proudly served to defend our freedoms, we must provide them with the care and benefits they have earned.

Big news for Buffalo! The Smithsonian’s Voices and Votes: Democracy in America exhibit is coming to the Michigan Street African American Heritage Corridor Commission from August 8 to September 19.

This powerful exhibit explores the fight for democracy – from the revolution to civil rights, from suffrage to casting ballots – and asks us: who gets to have a voice in our democracy?

It’s an opportunity to reflect, engage, and be inspired by the ongoing work of forming a more perfect union. Don’t miss it!

For more info, check out: https://t.co/YAOGED8ICX or https://t.co/jsPVbeNNGL

Today we commemorate the Voting Rights Act of 1965 – a landmark achievement born of generations of struggle, sacrifice, and unshakable courage. It was a promise that the voice of all Americans, regardless of race, would be heard at the ballot box. 

But that promise is under threat. From voter suppression laws to a broken campaign finance system, our democracy faces real danger. 

We honor the legacy of the Voting Rights Act not just with remembrance, but with action. The road ahead demands we restore and strengthen voting rights, protect fair elections, and ensure every voice counts. The fight for a just and representative democracy is far from over – and I won’t stop fighting until it’s fulfilled.

I joined Protect Our Care NY to mark 60 years of Medicare and Medicaid – programs that have kept generations of Americans healthy and secure.

But right now, those programs are under attack. Trump’s Big Ugly Law threatens to gut health care for 17 million Americans, including tens of thousands right here in Western New York.

These cuts aren’t abstract – they’re personal, and they’ll devastate our communities. I am fighting to #CancelTheCuts and protect the care New Yorkers rely on.

Today, I visited the Niagara Falls Air Reserve Station to thank the servicemembers and civilian personnel who keep our region and our country safe. 

Their dedication and sacrifice represent the very best of Western New York, and I’ll keep fighting in Congress to ensure they have the resources and support they deserve.

I was proud to stand with community leaders and @CSEALocal1000  retirees to send a message to the Trump administration and Congressional Republicans: hands off our Social Security.  

The Trump Administration just admitted what we’ve known all along, their so-called “Trump Accounts” are a backdoor attempt to privatize Social Security. These accounts don’t protect Americans in a market crash, don’t cover everyone, and don’t come close to replacing the stability Social Security provides. 

I’m proud to cosponsor the Social Security 2100 Act to strengthen and expand the program – not dismantle it. Social Security is a sacred promise. We will not allow anyone to gamble with Americans’ retirement or push millions back into poverty. Not on our watch.

I had the honor of joining Buffalo’s vibrant Burmese community for a powerful discussion.

We talked about the urgent need to restore U.S. humanitarian aid, to fight back against Trump’s cruel travel bans, and to secure the release of U.S. citizen and Buddhist Monk U Pyinya Zawta who is unjustly imprisoned by Burma’s military regime.

As your representative in Congress, I want you to know this: I see you, I hear you, and I’m fighting for you in Washington.

Your stories matter. Your struggles matter. And your future in this country matters. We’re in this together. Let’s keep pushing for justice – at home and abroad.

Proud to join @GovKathyHochul at @SUNYNiagara to make clear: Trump and Congressional Republicans’ Big Ugly Law is a complete betrayal of working families. 

Under these Republican cuts: 42 million Americans face losing SNAP benefits, 1 in 4 nursing homes are at risk of closure due to Medicaid cuts, ACA premiums will skyrocket, and nearly 17 million Americans will lose health coverage. 

Republicans in Washington are pushing an immoral agenda that will weaken our nation. Democrats are united at every level. We are fighting like hell to #CanceltheCuts and protect the programs that keep our communities strong.

This #NationalHealthCenterWeek, I stood with the incredible team at Neighborhood Health Center (@nhcwny)  to send a clear message: healthcare is a right, not a privilege.

As a former occupational therapist, and the son and grandson of a nurse, I’ve seen the life-changing impact of quality, accessible care. Community health centers are on the frontlines, keeping our neighborhoods healthy against all odds.

Meanwhile, Trump and Congressional Republicans passed over $1 trillion in healthcare cuts that will leave 17 million Americans uninsured. That’s unacceptable. 285,000 people in WNY rely on Medicaid. One in eight New Yorkers depend on a community health center for care. These are our children, our seniors, our veterans, and our neighbors.

We can’t let them down. I’m calling on my Republican colleagues to #CanceltheCuts. Our families and health centers deserve better.

Congratulations to all the organizers of this year’s Irish Festival on an extraordinary weekend celebrating Irish culture. I especially want to thank @SullivansBrewCo, the @BufIrishCenter, Rince na Tiarna, and everyone else who took part for helping make the festival such a success!

I’m proud to see the Irish traditions, music, and community spirit that have shaped Western New York on full display. Sláinte to another amazing year! ☘️

Proud to join the hardworking men and women of Union Concrete & Construction last night to celebrate 75 years of grit, pride, and progress.

From bridges and highways to the public works projects that power our region, this family-owned, union-built company has shaped Western New York’s infrastructure and economy for generations. 

Congratulations to Gary, Deborah, and Carley Hill on this incredible milestone! And of course, it's always great to catch up with my good friend Charlie Sickler. Here’s to 75 years strong!

Wishing a very happy 100th birthday to the legendary Hall of Fame Coach Marv Levy!

Coach, your leadership, grit, and unforgettable words — “Where else would you rather be than right here, right now?” — still echo through Buffalo and inspire generations.

Thank you for everything you’ve given to our city and to the game. Here’s to many more years of greatness! Go Bills! 🦬🎉
I am appalled by the findings of the OIG report on the failures in care at the Batavia Community Living Center. See my full statement below. https://t.co/OYSoZI7Ush

Calling all middle and high school students interested in coding! Submit an app for the 2025 @CongressionalAC by October 30th! #Congress4CS

For more information, visit: https://t.co/roycxmOkRh https://t.co/gSk4El52PE

I want to thank @FeedMoreWNY for opening their doors, and more importantly for opening their hearts to Western New Yorkers every single day. 

Last year, FeedMore saw a 16% increase in the need for nutritional assistance from local families here in WNY. At a time when that need is greater than ever, Congressional Republicans’ enacted the largest cut to SNAP in history, ripping food off the tables of children, seniors, and people with disabilities.

Nearly 42 million Americans, including over 139,000 Western New Yorkers in my district, rely on SNAP to put food on the table. These cuts will deepen poverty and worsen hunger – all so billionaires get more tax breaks. 

For the sake of communities like Western New York, we must #CanceltheCuts.

https://t.co/enc7eK6fuy

Gun violence is an epidemic – and instead of strengthening enforcement, the Trump administration is actively trying to weaken the very agency tasked with keeping our communities safe.

I led 47 of my colleagues in demanding the administration reverse course and stop undermining the ATF and critical federal gun safety laws.

Rolling back background checks, ignoring bad dealers, and gutting oversight puts lives at risk. We won’t stand for it.

With the passage of their Big Ugly Law, Trump and Congressional Republicans enacted the largest cut to SNAP in history, ripping food off the tables of children, seniors, and people with disabilities.

In Western New York alone, more than 139,000 people will be impacted, including 49,000 children, 20,000 seniors, and 12,000 individuals with disabilities - all to fund tax breaks for the wealthy on the backs of people who are struggling to eat.

@feedmorewny is already on the frontlines, feeding kids, supporting seniors, and stepping in when families' paychecks fall short. Congressional Republicans have made their work nearly impossible and turned a hunger crisis into a catastrophe.

Congressional Republicans need to get back to Washington and #CancelTheCuts, because in the wealthiest country on earth, no one should go hungry.

The murder of a brave NYPD officer and several innocent civilians in Midtown Manhattan is tragic and horrifying. We mourn their loss and stand with their loved ones and all those affected by this senseless act of violence.

We owe our deepest gratitude to the first responders who acted swiftly and selflessly to prevent an even greater loss of life.

This mass shooting is a devastating reminder that the epidemic of gun violence continues to plague our nation. The fact that a gunman crossed the country to carry out mass murder, despite a documented history of mental health crises, should alarm every one of us.

We cannot accept this as normal. We must confront the dangerous intersection of mental illness and easy access to deadly weapons. We are long overdue for stronger gun laws at the federal level and Congress has a responsibility to act.

New Yorkers are resilient, but they deserve more than thoughts and prayers. They deserve solutions.

https://t.co/4K1u6vnQTa

What a great weekend celebrating the Buffalo Italian Festival in the heart of North Buffalo — incredible food, lively music, and a proud community coming together to honor and celebrate Italian heritage! https://t.co/qikeQxtEQu

I was honored to attend a homecoming celebration of Father Tony Rigoli at St. Rose of Lima Church during Friday evenings mass!

Father Rigoli is a dear friend who I met 30 years ago at D’Youville University. He is a wonderful leader of the faith, a mentor, and an advocate for all people. The people of St. Guadalupe Church in New Orleans are blessed to have him leading the ministry.

Thrilled to join the Veterans Picnic and Pig Roast at the Agustin Olivencia Community Center to honor the Hispanic community’s long history and contributions in Western New York, and to thank our veterans for their sacrifice and service.

It is always a privilege to stand with dear friends, our veterans, and the Gabriel A. Rodriguez American Legion Post 1928, as we celebrate their vital role in our community.

There are few forces in this world more unifying and uplifting than gospel music. Buffalo’s 39th Annual Gospelfest isn’t just about great music – it’s about faith, history, and hope. 

Gospel music tells the stories of our nation’s past. It reminds us of where we’ve been and gives us the strength for where we’re going. Honored to enjoy the soundtrack for justice, healing, and love with my fellow Buffalonians.

I had a great time at Legislator Taisha St. Jean-Tard’s @Eriecountyld2 Carnival, connecting with neighbors and celebrating the strength and spirit of our community.
